description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dedicated and motivated person to take on the role of a Band 3 Healthcare Support Worker for the Community Children&#39;s Nursing team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting and varied role and the successful candidate will be required to work as part of the Team supporting children and young people in a range of community settings including children&#39;s outpatient clinics, children&#39;s homes and in schools.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Candidates must possess a Level 3 qualification in health and social care or an equivalent level 3 qualification. the candidate will have experience of working with children and young people and ideally have experience of working with children with complex healthcare needs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Training and support will be given to the successful applicant to enable them to deliver aspects of the role, for example venepuncture and enteral feeding.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Powys Teaching Health Board offers a comprehensive induction programme and the post holder would be given the opportunity to develop their knowledge, experience and skills within a friendly and supportive environment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you believe that you have the unique qualities that are needed to work with a small friendly team, and with children and their families, then we would like to hear from you. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKatie LangfordJob titleTeam Leader,Community Children&#39;s Nursing TeamEmail addresskatie.langford@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01686617455Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katie Langford on 01686 617445&lt;/p&gt;
